This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a meta approach to learning with noisy labels using deep neural networks. It also involves the use of gradient descent and gradient ascent, which are common optimization techniques in machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it mentions the use of deep neural networks for image classification tasks. Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as they are also relevant to the topic of deep learning and neural networks.
